Text.Value: Normal. Mostly. Didn't have much of an appetite at dinner, though he said he was saving himself for tonight.

EditorData.NodeContext: Hesitating, having second thoughts now she looks back on events

Text.Value: I'm wondering that myself...
A party in the sewers?
He did seem quite interested in my collar bones... I thought that was just his 'thing', if you catch my drift.

EditorData.NodeContext: Uncertain, seeing things in a new light

Text.Value: A vampire?! No... he wasn't... was he?
You sure he didn't try?
You're right. I'm sure he was perfectly safe.
I'm sure he'll turn up eventually - just wish there was somewhere to sit down that wasn't... sticky.
You have no idea...
You think something's happened to him?
Perhaps he lost his appetite.
Oh, go on, then. I'll tell you. It's an underground party. At a place called 'The Palace'.
I don't know if I should say - it's very exclusive...
*The individual descriptions could refer to many things, but taken together, she can only be referring to something vampiric in nature.*
I bloody hope so - my feet are getting soaked with gods know what. This party had better be worth it.
My date's supposed to meet me here, but there's no sign of him.
I'm sure he'll show up eventually.
Ah - a friendly face at last. Are you going to the party as well?
You know what - I might give this party a miss. Plenty more fish in the Chionthar, as they say.

EditorData.NodeContext: Nervous - realised she needs to get out of here

Text.Value: He was so enthusiastic. I don't understand why he hasn't shown up...
You haven't seen him, have you? Pale, skinny - extremely piercing eyes.
It's funny. He was ever so keen for me to come. He didn't seem the type to cancel...
Mother may I. I'm positively starved.
Looks a bit like your friend here.
Now that you mention it, he didn't eat much at dinner last night. Didn't eat anything at all - just pushed the food round his plate.
I very much doubt you're going where I'm going.
I'd cut your losses if I were you.
The venue's called 'The Palace'. Not sure what it stands for, but it sounds very exclusive.
I'm sure that's what he's doing...

EditorData.NodeContext: sarcastic, he's definitely not just washing his hair

Text.Value: I'll give him a while longer. Maybe he's just washing his hair...
I know. Bit strange, isn't it? But then you have to be open to trying new things.
Did he say what kind of party it's supposed to be?
I'll be honest with you - he could turn out to be a worg in a skin suit, and it still wouldn't be the worst date I've had.
Was there anything else unique about this date of yours?
I'm sure he'll show up eventually.
You've had a very lucky escape. Your date was a vampire.
Ah, of course. The party's a secret - don't worry, I'm in the know.

EditorData.NodeContext: verbal equivalent of a knowing tap on the nose

Text.Value: Oh dear. I assure you it's not.
Looks a bit like you, actually.
Which party is that? I get so many invitations...
I'd imagine so - there's no way he'd leave someone as appetising as you alone.

EditorData.logicalname: INCLUSION LINE: DIDN'T VISIT CAZADOR'S PALACE

Text.Value: Now you mention it, he brought his own wine with him to the Mermaid last night. Strange smell it had, kind of metallic...

EditorData.NodeContext: Starts off gossipping, then realises what he was really drinking (blood)

Text.Value: I know the Mermaid's food's an acquired taste, but you'd think he'd at least have tried it... I bet he was nervous. He seemed really keen.
What type did he seem?
But then... why am I still here? He could have had me by the neck any time he liked...
You're right. Just look at me - up to my ankles in filth, waiting for a man with a collarbone fetish. I deserve better!
Only that it was him and a few of his closest friends. Said he couldn't wait to introduce me to them - how often does a man say that to a girl he's only met once?
If you see him, don't tell him I was here. Just tell him I, erm, I wasn't ready to be in a relationship. I'm sure he'll understand.

Synopsis: The player meets a lady waiting for her Vampire Boyfriend. The player can persuade her to leave.
